2
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:59,710
Your media player does not support the subtitle format used in this episode.
Subtitles will likely not function properly.
Please use one of the recommended video players, preferably mpv:
https://mpv.io

3
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:58,720
Where the heck is he?!
It's already morning!

4
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:04,480
He's forty-six minutes late!
We're going to miss the current!

5
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:08,730
With all that heavy gold, it'd take
him even longer to come back!

6
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:11,860
There's no way he took
that into consideration!

7
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:15,240
No, I don't think the time was
ever a consideration for him here.

8
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,700
Yeah, 100 percent.

9
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:19,450
Do you think he got beat up?

10
00:02:19,830 --> 00:02:21,500
By that Bellamy guy?!

11
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,420
If he did, time would be
the least of his problems!

12
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,920
What the hell, Nami?

13
00:02:30,670 --> 00:02:33,680
Hey!

14
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,470
It's him! Thank goodness! He's back!

15
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:42,350
I did it!

16
00:02:42,350 --> 00:02:45,730
Hurry up, Luffy!
We're behind schedule!

17
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:47,270
Check it out!

18
00:02:47,270 --> 00:02:51,320
A Hercules! It took
forever to find one!

19
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,690
You were looking...

20
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:54,070
...for a beetle?!

21
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:05,040
Whoa! Awesome!

22
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,830
The Going Merry: Flight Mode!

23
00:03:07,830 --> 00:03:09,710
It looks like it can fly!

24
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:13,010
Right?! It's all thanks to them!

25
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:18,720
Look at 'em go.

26
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:21,470
I get uneasy just looking at it...

27
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,600
Same here.

28
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:26,940
Even a pigeon would've
been better than a chicken...

29
00:03:26,940 --> 00:03:29,730
You think that's the issue?!
You're an idiot!

30
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:33,400
Alright! Let's set sail!
Is everyone ready?!

31
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,740
– Aye aye, sir!
– Aye aye, sir!

32
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:42,950
Get on board already! There's no time!

33
00:03:42,950 --> 00:03:47,040
Or do you wanna waste your only
ticket into the sky, you fool?

34
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,460
Right! Thanks for the ship!

35
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:55,550
It's them you should thank.

36
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:58,720
Yeah! Thanks, you guys!

37
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,220
My Hercules... is yours!

38
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:05,730
– Really?! For us?!
– Seriously?!

39
00:04:05,730 --> 00:04:08,100
– What a great guy!
– What a great guy!

40
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:11,310
Anyway, we gotta go!
Get on board before it's too late!

41
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:14,190
We'll lead the way, so follow us!

42
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:16,070
Luffy! Hurry!

43
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,450
Yeah!

44
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:28,120
That "City of Gold" is just
a figment of Noland's imagination!

45
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,500
Saruyama Alliance!

46
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,460
Don't screw this up!

47
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:41,720
No matter what happens, we'll back
them up with everything we've got!

48
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,890
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

49
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,890
Alright! Let's go!

50
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:53,440
Everyone, time to set sail!

51
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,400
All right!

52
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,230
Aye, Nami dearest!

53
00:05:08,410 --> 00:05:11,920
This is where we part ways, kid!

54
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,960
Yeah!

55
00:05:14,710 --> 00:05:18,920
There's one thing that I know for sure.

56
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:18,920
Huh?

57
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:25,890
No one has ever disproved the existence
of the City of Gold or the sky island.

58
00:05:25,890 --> 00:05:26,890
Right!

59
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:33,940
People might laugh at my faulty logic,
but it's good enough for me.

60
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:36,610
That's what romance is!

61
00:05:36,610 --> 00:05:38,070
Romance...

62
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,700
That's right!

63
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,830
Thanks for the gold.

64
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:53,540
Don't go falling from
the sky now, alright?!

65
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,920
See ya, chestnut head!

66
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:00,460
Thanks for everything, Cricket!

67
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:05,260
Mister, the City of Gold
definitely exists!

68
00:06:05,260 --> 00:06:08,430
Chestnut head!
Don't do anything reckless!

69
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:10,730
Mind your own business!

70
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:20,400
It's morning already!

71
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:23,200
Well? See anything?

72
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:26,570
I can't see any trace of the shore yet!

73
00:06:26,570 --> 00:06:29,660
Are those guys really
going to the sky island?

74
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:32,000
Yeah, that's what they said.

75
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,460
It'll be tough to follow 'em,
so let's settle things before that.

76
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:40,500
Listen up! It's seven o'clock!

77
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:45,050
We should arrive at our
destination around eleven!

78
00:06:45,050 --> 00:06:49,510
Like the boss said,
 the Knock-Up Stream's exact location

79
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:56,520
changes each time, so we
need to arrive early to find it!

80
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:58,770
Look! Look!

81
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:01,980
We're a little behind schedule, so...

82
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:05,610
Hey! Are you listening to me?

83
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:07,820
See! It looked forward!

84
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:12,200
There sure are some
weird birds out there!

85
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:17,330
It's true! He can only face south!
This guy's a compass! How funny!

86
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:22,670
What'd he say?

87
00:07:23,170 --> 00:07:26,590
He said he's going to face
a different direction to mess us up.

88
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:29,640
Go ahead and try!

89
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,980
Oh! He faced north!

90
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:45,360
He only feels right when facing south!

91
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:50,530
Hey, you guys!
Don't make the big boss mad!

92
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:57,000
Leave them be! Though their
antics do make me nervous.

93
00:07:57,330 --> 00:07:58,960
Huh? What's wrong?

94
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:03,250
There's no point in being anxious!

95
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,670
Let's take it easy!

96
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:07,930
And who put us behind schedule?

97
00:08:08,430 --> 00:08:13,510
He's right! There's no point in
being tense for hours on end!

98
00:08:13,510 --> 00:08:18,520
I see! Right, men!
Full speed ahead, while relaxing!

99
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,900
What nice weather!

100
00:08:27,030 --> 00:08:28,490
Are we gonna be okay?

101
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:31,700
Boss! Bad news!

102
00:08:30,790 --> 00:08:31,700
What's wrong?!

103
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:35,160
Night's coming from the southwest!
Cumuloimperator clouds!

104
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,580
Seriously?! What time is it?!

105
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:40,750
Ten o'clock!
Way earlier than expected!

106
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,130
This is bad... Can we make it, Shojo?!

107
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:45,700
Utan Divers! Into the sea immediately!

108
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,170
Look for currents!

109
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,010
It's the cumuloimperator clouds!

110
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,390
What's happening?!

111
00:08:55,510 --> 00:09:00,600
They appeared sooner than expected,
and we still don't know where the current is!

112
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:12,700
The sonar pinged! Large current
detected at twelve o'clock!

113
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:16,660
Large unidentified creature at
nine o'clock! I believe it's a sea king!

114
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:20,620
Waves clashing against
the current at ten o'clock!

115
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:22,670
Likely a giant whirlpool!

116
00:09:22,670 --> 00:09:26,130
That's it! Point the ship
toward ten o'clock!

117
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:29,920
It's an indication of the explosion!
Catch the whirlpool! Don't let up!

118
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,850
What the...?!

119
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:39,100
The waves suddenly got taller!

120
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:39,100
We're gonna sink!

121
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:43,940
It's the earthquake before
the explosion! Get ready!

122
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,560
E-Explosion?!

123
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:47,020
Miss Navigator!

124
00:09:47,690 --> 00:09:49,240
What's the log pose saying?

125
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,840
It keeps pointing to those clouds!

126
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,490
The sky island is up there?!

127
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,790
The wind's perfect, too!

128
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:02,500
The clouds are headed for
the heart of the whirlpool!

129
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,920
Wait! What whirlpool?
Where do you see one?

130
00:10:06,590 --> 00:10:09,760
Looks like we hit
the jackpot this time, Brother!

131
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:13,180
Yeah! The explosion looks
like it'll be big enough, too!

132
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:14,550
So we can make it?!

133
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,970
We sure can!

134
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:18,850
Huh?

135
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:21,140
We'll get you into
the whirlpool's vortex!

136
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,560
What do we do after that?!

137
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:27,940
Ride the current! If you can get to
the center, things should work out!

138
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,400
The center of this massive whirlpool?!

139
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:38,370
Nobody said anything
about being sucked in!

140
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:41,870
It's all right! I'll protect you and Robin!

141
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,540
I've never seen such
a large whirlpool...

142
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:50,880
Holy crap! This is bad!
Let's turn back! Let me go back!

143
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:54,180
Just accept it, Usopp! It's too late.
Someone is already sucked in.

144
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:56,680
Let's go! Sky island!

145
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:20,950
Alright, you guys!

146
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:24,960
You're on your own now! Good luck!

147
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,080
Right! Thanks for the lift!

148
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:28,080
Hold on!

149
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:32,340
Let me off, will you?!
I'm scared out of my wits here!

150
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:34,260
Let me go back, you jerk!

151
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:36,090
We're all gonna die!

152
00:11:36,090 --> 00:11:39,510
Nobody said anything about
a giant whirlpool! They tricked us!

153
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,060
It's night!

154
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:44,560
The whirlpool is
sucking us in really fast!

155
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:48,060
Let's go back, Luffy!
We still have time!

156
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:51,860
Don't you understand?! This
whirlpool alone is enough to kill us!

157
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,690
The sky island's
a dream within a dream!

158
00:11:53,690 --> 00:11:56,200
A dream within a dream?
You think so?

159
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:59,530
Yes, Luffy! I don't think
we can do this after all!

160
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,910
An island in a dream within a dream!

161
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:05,790
I'd never forgive myself for
passing up an adventure like that!

162
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:09,420
– H-He's enjoying this...
– H-He's enjoying this...

163
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:16,220
Hey! While you guys are
over here pointlessly whining...

164
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:17,380
Yeah? What?

165
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:22,640
We're being pulled into it!

166
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:28,730
Now, Nami! Seek shelter in my arms!

167
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:31,790
We're falling in!

168
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,820
What?! It disappeared?! How come?!

169
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:39,910
What happened?!

170
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:44,830
Th-That huge whirlpool...
What's going on here?!

171
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:54,340
No! It's already started!

172
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,460
Huh?

173
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:58,800
The whirlpool just vanished!

174
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:03,300
Y-You don't mean...

175
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:05,810
Hold it!

176
00:13:08,850 --> 00:13:09,850
Hey, Zoro!

177
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:11,350
Look!

178
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:23,620
I caught up to ya, Straw Hat Luffy!

179
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,200
He was in Mock Town...!

180
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:29,330
Who?!

181
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:34,290
I came to collect that 100-million
head of yours! Prepare yourself!

182
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:42,340
Hey, who are they? Friends of yours?

183
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:44,970
Huh, I dunno.

184
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:50,770
Why's it dark around here?

185
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:53,900
My head? What do
you mean, 100 million?

186
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,270
So you don't know!

187
00:13:56,900 --> 00:14:01,650
There's a 100-million-belly
bounty on your head!

188
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:05,950
And Pirate Hunter Zoro!
You're worth 60 million!

189
00:14:05,950 --> 00:14:08,950
It's true! Those are
new wanted posters.

190
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:12,080
Zoro! You're a wanted man now!

191
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:16,290
What?! Hold on! What about me?!
There's one for me too, right?!

192
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:17,880
Uh... nope.

193
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:19,380
Look closer!

194
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:20,840
Not there.

195
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:27,010
That makes sense. Your bounties must've
shot up after the Alabasta incident!

196
00:14:27,010 --> 00:14:28,680
But 100 million...!

197
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:31,770
One hundred million!

198
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:34,400
Hear that?! I'm worth 100 million!

199
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,730
And I'm at 60 million!
Pretty lame, huh?

200
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:38,690
You shouldn't be celebrating that!

201
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:43,200
Hey, you guys! Don't get distracted!

202
00:14:47,070 --> 00:14:51,160
It's coming! The Knock-Up Stream!

203
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:54,120
Get ready!

204
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:57,460
What the...?

205
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:01,000
All hands! Hold on tight
or get in the cabin!

206
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:07,090
The ship is going up!

207
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:47,430
No good! The ship's gonna capsize!

208
00:15:49,890 --> 00:15:51,850
Everyone, grab on!

209
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:53,600
Don't get thrown overboard!

210
00:15:57,270 --> 00:16:00,440
– Go! To the sky island!
– Go! To the sky island!

211
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,860
What the heck's going on?!

212
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:07,320
The ship's going straight
up a pillar of water!

213
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,360
This is fun!

214
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,370
How is this possible?!

215
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:13,330
Wind?!

216
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:20,330
Alright! We can get to
the sky now! Go, Merry!

217
00:16:22,290 --> 00:16:25,760
Hold on! I don't think
it's gonna be that easy!

218
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:27,050
Wh-What's wrong?!

219
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:29,220
Huh? Did we forget something?

220
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:31,470
The hull's coming clear of the water!

221
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:32,550
Huh?!

222
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:35,560
If this keeps up, we're gonna
get sent flying to our doom!

223
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:41,310
B-B-But what do you w-want us to do?!
W-W-We can barely even h-hold on!

224
00:16:41,310 --> 00:16:43,270
Huh?! What's that?!

225
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:45,400
A sea king!

226
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,610
It's the one that got sucked in earlier!

227
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:55,540
See! It's only a matter of time
before that happens to us too!

228
00:16:55,540 --> 00:17:01,040
You say that, but we are
riding on a hell of an explosion!

229
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,500
Can we really help it?!

230
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,460
This is a natural disaster after all!

231
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:09,800
There's a bunch of stuff falling on us!

232
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:13,470
It's the victims of
the Knock-Up Stream!

233
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:18,520
We're goners! We're gonna
slam into the sea and die!

234
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:22,810
Spread the sails right now!

235
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:27,940
This is the sea, not just any
water pillar! It's a rising ocean current!

236
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:30,240
And the updraft is a rising air current

237
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,530
produced by the geothermal
heat and steam explosion!

238
00:17:34,070 --> 00:17:36,830
If we're dealing with wind
and sea, I can navigate it!

239
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,250
Who's this ship's navigator?!

240
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,250
It's Nami!

241
00:17:43,250 --> 00:17:46,380
Alright, men!
Do everything Nami says!

242
00:17:46,380 --> 00:17:47,710
– Aye!
– Aye!

243
00:17:47,710 --> 00:17:51,680
Catch the starboard wind,
turn the helm aport, and ride the current!

244
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:52,380
– Aye aye!
– Aye aye!

245
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:57,350
Oh, no! The ship is
about to leave the water!

246
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:00,810
We're gonna fall! We're gonna fall,
Nami! Do something, Nami!

247
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:02,770
No, we'll make it!

248
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,150
We're flying!

249
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:13,070
Awesome! The ship is flying!

250
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:14,450
Is this for real?!

251
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,370
We did it!

252
00:18:18,370 --> 00:18:19,790
Wow!

253
00:18:19,790 --> 00:18:22,210
Nami, you're amazing!

254
00:18:22,910 --> 00:18:25,670
And I love you!

255
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:30,590
